  "Metadata": {
    "RepoURL": "git@github.com:essensys-hub/essensys-user-portal-backend.git",
    "Branch": "main",
    "Commit": "032a80663ded900b4f77cfcf070ab177b76b3930",
    "CommitMsg": "security: fail-closed secrets + move OAuth token to URL fragment\n\nHIGH #1 — Fail closed on weak/missing secrets:\n- config.Validate() rejects empty, too-short (\u003c16), or known-insecure\n  JWT_SECRET / ADMIN_TOKEN at startup (cmd/server/main.go log.Fatal).\n- Remove insecure literal fallbacks (default-insecure-jwt-secret-change-me,\n  essensys-admin-secret, insecure-dev-secret) from middleware and admin login.\n- Constant-time compare for the static ADMIN_TOKEN; never match an empty token.\n\nHIGH #2 — OAuth session token no longer placed in the URL query string:\n- Google and Apple callbacks now redirect with the JWT in the URL fragment\n  (admin#token=...), which is not sent to the server, written to access logs,\n  or leaked via the Referer header.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
    "Author": "rhinosys \u003cnicolas.rineau@rhinosys.fr\u003e",
    "Committer": "rhinosys \u003cnicolas.rineau@rhinosys.fr\u003e"
  },
